Habitat. The single specimen of
O . luciae
was taken in Wet Chaco (
Dinerstein et al . 1995
), in a savanna composed of palms (
Copernicia alba
), native bunch grasses, and bare ground, with small interspersed islands of semideciduous forest. The savanna floods periodically from the Paraguay River (
Fig. 6
).
